Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportPinDensityMap(25.10)                          reportPinDensityMap(25.10)

Name
       reportPinDensityMap - Generates a map that uses colors to represent pin
       density and generates a pin density report

Syntax
       reportPinDensityMap

       [-help]

       [-displayStep <step_value>]

       [-gridInMicron <micron>]

       [-gridInRow <numberRow>]

       [-threshold <density>]

       Generates a map that uses colors to represent pin density and generates
       a pin density report. Use this command any time after placement.

       You can also use setPinDensityMapMode to set the threshold, and specify
       whether the map displays bins in microns or rows.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each reportPinDensityMap parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man reportPinDensityMap

       -displayStep <step_value>
              Specifies the range step for displaying the pin density map.

              Default: 0.05

       -gridInMicron <micron>
              Specifies the horizontal or vertical dimension of a bin  in  the
              map in microns.

              Default: 50

              Minimum: 0.000000

              Maximum: 1000.000000

       -gridInRow <numberRow>
              Specifies  the  value (in row-height) of side of square grid for
              pin density calculations.

              Default: 10

              Minimum: 1

              Maximum: 100

        -threshold <density>
              Specifies a threshold density value  over  which  the  densities
              must  be reported. Any grid under the threshold value is not re-
              ported. The value must be positive.

              Default: 0.5

              Minimum: 0.000000

              Maximum: 2.000000

Examples
       The following command reports the pin density map:

       reportPinDensityMap

       *** Starting report pin density ***

       default core: bins with pin density > 0.5 = 0 % (0 / 1)

       bin size: 90 sites by 10 row(s). total 1 bins ( 1 by 1 )

        pin density range   #bins     %

        total                 0       0

